00:00:03.880 --> 00:00:05.840
OSSAMA ALAMI: Hello, everybody,
and welcome to

00:00:05.840 --> 00:00:07.710
Bring Your App to
the Big Screen.

00:00:07.710 --> 00:00:11.560
This session is all about
designing TV applications,

00:00:11.560 --> 00:00:13.860
designing for Google TV.

00:00:13.860 --> 00:00:17.260
Before we get started, my
name's Ossama Alami.

00:00:17.260 --> 00:00:20.260
I manage the Developer Relations
team for Google TV,

00:00:20.260 --> 00:00:22.400
and I'm co-presenting here
today with Michael

00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:25.762
Sundermeyer, who leads
our UX team.

00:00:25.762 --> 00:00:27.190
[SCATTERED APPLAUSE]

00:00:27.190 --> 00:00:30.390
OSSAMA ALAMI: Big
fans of Michael.

00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:34.180
So by show of hands, can I see
how many of you are Android

00:00:34.180 --> 00:00:37.230
developers or have built
an Android app?

00:00:37.230 --> 00:00:38.010
Great.

00:00:38.010 --> 00:00:40.440
I think that's about half.

00:00:40.440 --> 00:00:44.640
And how many of you have built
an app for Google TV, either

00:00:44.640 --> 00:00:48.580
Android or a web app?

00:00:48.580 --> 00:00:50.720
A smattering.

00:00:50.720 --> 00:00:53.360
So this session is going to be
a great for those of you that

00:00:53.360 --> 00:00:56.600
have built apps and great for
those of you that haven't.

00:00:56.600 --> 00:01:01.430
The biggest thing to building
a TV application is probably

00:01:01.430 --> 00:01:06.550
design, because it's very
different from mobile or

00:01:06.550 --> 00:01:09.730
tablets or even PC
or web design.

00:01:09.730 --> 00:01:14.300
Designing for TV is designing
for a different user

00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:16.860
experience.

00:01:16.860 --> 00:01:20.710
So as a refresher, I'll go over
what Google TV is for

00:01:20.710 --> 00:01:22.760
those of you that don't know.

00:01:22.760 --> 00:01:27.720
Google TV is Android
optimized for TV.

00:01:27.720 --> 00:01:30.030
It comes with Google Chrome,
and it comes with Google

00:01:30.030 --> 00:01:33.810
services like search, a
discovery experience called TV

00:01:33.810 --> 00:01:38.910
and Movies, photos, YouTube,
and other applications.

00:01:38.910 --> 00:01:40.620
And it comes with live
TV integration.

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:45.290
So Google TV is really about
integrating the live TV with

00:01:45.290 --> 00:01:48.600
the web, bringing the best of TV
and the best of the web and

00:01:48.600 --> 00:01:51.140
trying to make it the best
experience possible, bring as

00:01:51.140 --> 00:01:53.900
much content as possible to the
user where they're looking

00:01:53.900 --> 00:01:56.190
to be entertained when they're
on the couch in

00:01:56.190 --> 00:01:58.980
front of their TV.

00:01:58.980 --> 00:02:03.460
So last October, we launched a
major update to Google TV.

00:02:03.460 --> 00:02:07.160
We vastly simplified the UI,
the user experience.

00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:09.690
We improved search
and discovery.

00:02:09.690 --> 00:02:13.290
We released a new YouTube
experience for Google TV.

00:02:13.290 --> 00:02:17.420
And critically, for most of you
guys, we launched Android

00:02:17.420 --> 00:02:20.460
Market, now Google Play, and the
ability for you to build

00:02:20.460 --> 00:02:24.655
applications and reach users
on their TVs and distribute

00:02:24.655 --> 00:02:27.680
those applications through
Google Play.

00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:31.960
So a lot of what we learned in
simplifying the UI and making

00:02:31.960 --> 00:02:36.150
a better user experience in our
second-generation software

00:02:36.150 --> 00:02:37.400
we're going to teach
you about today.

00:02:40.340 --> 00:02:43.864
They're very exciting in
the session next door.

00:02:43.864 --> 00:02:44.780
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

00:02:44.780 --> 00:02:45.700
OSSAMA ALAMI: There we go.

00:02:45.700 --> 00:02:46.270
Yeah!

00:02:46.270 --> 00:02:50.940
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE CONTINUE]

00:02:50.940 --> 00:02:53.320
OSSAMA ALAMI: Thank
you for that.

00:02:53.320 --> 00:02:56.270
I'm sure you're all very excited
about our new devices.

00:02:56.270 --> 00:02:58.630
We have new devices that
launched this week and over

00:02:58.630 --> 00:02:59.860
the last couple weeks.

00:02:59.860 --> 00:03:01.510
They're out in the sandbox.

00:03:01.510 --> 00:03:03.850
On this level, I encourage you
guys to check them out.

00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:05.970
I'm very excited about
these things.

00:03:05.970 --> 00:03:08.700
They all have the
ARM processor.

00:03:08.700 --> 00:03:12.120
They're shipping in the US, and
the Sony devices are going

00:03:12.120 --> 00:03:14.520
to be available internationally.

00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:18.630
So Sony has released a buddy
box, and they have a Blu-ray

00:03:18.630 --> 00:03:20.220
player that they're demoing.

00:03:20.220 --> 00:03:23.760
Vizio released a buddy box
earlier this week.

00:03:23.760 --> 00:03:27.890
And LG has a series of TVs
with Google TV built in.

00:03:27.890 --> 00:03:30.040
And I'm happy to announce that
later this summer we'll be

00:03:30.040 --> 00:03:33.430
releasing an updated Google
Play store for Google TV.

00:03:33.430 --> 00:03:36.670
This will add some the features
you heard about

00:03:36.670 --> 00:03:38.980
yesterday, subscription billing
support, partial

00:03:38.980 --> 00:03:42.050
updates, as well as the ability
for users to purchase

00:03:42.050 --> 00:03:48.060
music, videos, and now TV shows
directly from their TV.

00:03:48.060 --> 00:03:50.410
This is the first year we're
doing a full track for Google

00:03:50.410 --> 00:03:52.970
TV at IO, and I'm really excited
about this session and

00:03:52.970 --> 00:03:53.710
the other sessions.

00:03:53.710 --> 00:03:55.310
I'm going to quickly tell
you about the other

00:03:55.310 --> 00:03:56.730
two sessions we have.

00:03:56.730 --> 00:04:01.250
If you're interested about DRM,
streaming video, and the

00:04:01.250 --> 00:04:03.492
enhancements that we made to
Google TV there, if you're

00:04:03.492 --> 00:04:06.160
interested about getting your
content on TV, I encourage you

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:09.720
to check out this session
after lunch.

00:04:09.720 --> 00:04:13.070
And today a lot of TV users
are distracted users.

00:04:13.070 --> 00:04:15.430
They're sitting on their couch
with a mobile phone or a

00:04:15.430 --> 00:04:19.550
tablet or a PC, a laptop.

00:04:19.550 --> 00:04:22.680
And part of the time they're
watching TV, they're also on

00:04:22.680 --> 00:04:23.920
those devices.

00:04:23.920 --> 00:04:27.930
So if you want to learn how to
build a unique experience that

00:04:27.930 --> 00:04:30.620
connects the user on their
second screen device, on their

00:04:30.620 --> 00:04:33.910
mobile phone or tablet, as well
as on the TV that they're

00:04:33.910 --> 00:04:36.440
watching, build a cohesive
experience around your

00:04:36.440 --> 00:04:39.225
application, go to this session,
and we'll teach you a

00:04:39.225 --> 00:04:43.550
little about the technologies we
have to make that possible.

00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:44.580
So why do you care?

00:04:44.580 --> 00:04:46.240
Why do you care about
building for TV?

00:04:46.240 --> 00:04:49.240
TVs have been around for a long
time, and it turns out

00:04:49.240 --> 00:04:51.180
there are a whole lot of them.

00:04:51.180 --> 00:04:54.040
In the US, there are more
TVs than people.

00:04:54.040 --> 00:05:00.360
On average, 2 and 1/2 people
in a home and 2.93 TV sets.

00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:03.830
This stat is actually going up,
even though the rise of

00:05:03.830 --> 00:05:06.030
smartphones and tablets.

00:05:06.030 --> 00:05:08.480
People continue to watch TV.

00:05:08.480 --> 00:05:10.150
People continue to buy TVs.

00:05:10.150 --> 00:05:14.850
This is really about meeting
the user in the

00:05:14.850 --> 00:05:16.000
living room, right?

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:19.630
Meeting the user where they're
looking to be entertained.

00:05:19.630 --> 00:05:21.150
And they still want to be
entertained on their

00:05:21.150 --> 00:05:22.310
televisions.

00:05:22.310 --> 00:05:24.840
And they watch a whole
lot of television.

00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:29.300
In the US, on average, five
hours of TV per day.

00:05:29.300 --> 00:05:32.680
So this is an opportunity for
you guys as developers to

00:05:32.680 --> 00:05:38.390
finally meet the users with the
five hours of TV watching

00:05:38.390 --> 00:05:42.160
they're doing per day as well
as the other amount of time

00:05:42.160 --> 00:05:43.920
that the TV sits off.

00:05:43.920 --> 00:05:48.340
Think about an experience
that is uniquely

00:05:48.340 --> 00:05:51.060
appropriate for the TV.

00:05:51.060 --> 00:05:52.920
And it continues to grow.

00:05:52.920 --> 00:05:56.200
So this stat's by
DisplaySearch.

00:05:56.200 --> 00:05:58.800
By 2015, over 500 million
connected

00:05:58.800 --> 00:05:59.990
TVs will have shipped.

00:05:59.990 --> 00:06:02.920
Connected TVs or smart TVs.

00:06:02.920 --> 00:06:08.920
And that year, 47% of flat
panels shipped that year will

00:06:08.920 --> 00:06:11.050
be smart TVs.

00:06:11.050 --> 00:06:16.210
So Google TV really aims to be
an open app platform for you

00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:19.320
guys as developers to build
applications and for

00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:24.070
manufacturers to build
a smart TV.

00:06:24.070 --> 00:06:28.970
Users are become accustomed
having access on the content

00:06:28.970 --> 00:06:31.740
that they love on all
of their devices.

00:06:31.740 --> 00:06:33.550
That includes the TV now.

00:06:33.550 --> 00:06:37.500
If you have an application that
is meant to entertain or

00:06:37.500 --> 00:06:40.690
maybe inform the user, it's
a great TV application.

00:06:40.690 --> 00:06:43.780
And users, as they get more
and more familiar with

00:06:43.780 --> 00:06:46.080
connected TVs and smart TVs,
are really going to

00:06:46.080 --> 00:06:48.730
want that app there.

00:06:48.730 --> 00:06:51.420
So reach and delight your users
where they're looking to

00:06:51.420 --> 00:06:52.870
be entertained.

00:06:52.870 --> 00:06:53.650
And how you do this?

00:06:53.650 --> 00:06:57.330
Well, there are two ways right
now to build for Google TV.

00:06:57.330 --> 00:07:00.640
It is an Android device, so you
can build an Android app.

00:07:00.640 --> 00:07:02.890
And it does ship with a full
desktop version of Google

00:07:02.890 --> 00:07:07.250
Chrome, so you can
build a web app.

00:07:07.250 --> 00:07:09.640
When I say build an Android app,
it's really just that.

00:07:09.640 --> 00:07:13.380
The Google TV SDK is
the Android SDK.

00:07:13.380 --> 00:07:15.230
What we're going to teach you
about in this session is how

00:07:15.230 --> 00:07:17.850
to design that app for TV.

00:07:17.850 --> 00:07:19.940
But if you already have
experience building Android

00:07:19.940 --> 00:07:21.540
applications, that's great.

00:07:21.540 --> 00:07:23.750
You already know most of
what you need to know

00:07:23.750 --> 00:07:25.210
to build a TV app.

00:07:25.210 --> 00:07:27.960
And you get the advantage of
distributing and monetizing

00:07:27.960 --> 00:07:31.150
that app and discoverability
options through Google

00:07:31.150 --> 00:07:34.780
Play on Google TV.

00:07:34.780 --> 00:07:37.850
Or build a web app.

00:07:37.850 --> 00:07:42.435
Your site's already accessible
on Chrome in Google TV, but

00:07:42.435 --> 00:07:44.920
what we're going to teach you
here today is how to optimize

00:07:44.920 --> 00:07:48.470
that experience for TV viewers,
how to make it really

00:07:48.470 --> 00:07:53.130
great on the web browser
that we ship with.

00:07:53.130 --> 00:07:55.750
Those are the two options for
building for Google TV.

00:07:55.750 --> 00:07:57.590
We're not going to go into the
depths of how to build an

00:07:57.590 --> 00:07:59.450
Android app or how to
build a web app.

00:07:59.450 --> 00:08:01.870
There's lots of sessions here
at I/O that'll teach you how

00:08:01.870 --> 00:08:02.620
to do that.

00:08:02.620 --> 00:08:04.400
What we're really going to do
is we're going to teach you

00:08:04.400 --> 00:08:07.130
how to design a great TV app.

00:08:07.130 --> 00:08:09.670
And since I'm not the
expert on that, I'm

00:08:09.670 --> 00:08:11.073
going to call up Michael.

00:08:11.073 --> 00:08:14.524
[APPLAUSE]

