Because most TVs still consume
linear in the evening when you

00:54:10.240 --> 00:54:12.200
have large [? demand ?]
for it.

00:54:12.200 --> 00:54:14.950
So how does Google TV-- because
you can't really do

00:54:14.950 --> 00:54:17.970
overlays over linear TV.

00:54:17.970 --> 00:54:18.160
OSSAMA ALAMI: Right.

00:54:18.160 --> 00:54:19.760
AUDIENCE: Commercial
problem, so--

00:54:19.760 --> 00:54:22.750
OSSAMA ALAMI: Currently we don't
support any way to embed

00:54:22.750 --> 00:54:26.060
or overlay over linear TV,
although it is a very common

00:54:26.060 --> 00:54:28.780
feature request from the
developer community.

00:54:28.780 --> 00:54:31.580
I think we're trying to solve
the user experience problem of

00:54:31.580 --> 00:54:37.690
how to do that right before we
expose it to the thousands of

00:54:37.690 --> 00:54:39.210
apps out there.

00:54:39.210 --> 00:54:42.560
And we want to make sure that
it remains a good user

00:54:42.560 --> 00:54:45.010
experience across
